  "text": "The mechanism of the increase in residual circulation in the lower stratosphere is well understood (e.g. [CITATION_1] . It follows the increase in upper tropospheric temperatures that leads to an upward shift and increase in the zonal mean winds. This can be seen in Fig. 9a , which shows the MMM differences of the zonal mean wind between the two time periods. Subsequently, the critical layers that allow for wave propagation shift to higher levels. This becomes evident from and 150 hPa. The enhanced wave dissipation in the lower stratosphere leads to amplified poleward residual transport, which reflects in ∆v * (Fig. 9c) .",
